  "title": "Service Engineer (Analytical Instruments, Class 3)",
  "description": "<ul>\n  <li>Install, commission, troubleshoot, and repair <strong>laboratory and analytical equipment.</strong></li>\n  <li>Provide on-site technical support, guidance, and timely corrective actions to customers.</li>\n  <li>Perform preventive maintenance and ensure equipment operates at optimal performance.</li>\n  <li>Prepare accurate service reports and interpret technical drawings and schematics.</li>\n  <li>Stay updated on new technologies and support continuous improvement of service quality.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>Requirements:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Diploma in Electronics, Electrical, Mechanical Engineering, or related field.</li>\n  <li>At least 2 years’ <strong>service/maintenance experience in scientific or analytical equipment.</strong></li>\n  <li>Strong hands-on troubleshooting skills and ability to read technical drawings/schematics.</li>\n  <li>Independent, detail-oriented, and able to work in a fast-paced, multi-tasking environment.</li>\n  <li>Possess a valid <strong>Class 3 licence</strong> is an advantage.</li>\n</ul>\n<p>If you are keen to apply for the position, kindly email your detailed resume in<strong> MS Word </strong>to <strong>hr@recruit-expert.com</strong></p>\n<p>Please note that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.</p>\n<p>For more job opportunities, please visit our website at <a href=\"http://www.recruit-expert.com/\"><strong>www.recruit-expert.com</strong></a></p>\n<p>EA Licence: 19C9701<br>\nRegistration: R21100996</p>",
